Jeff,

I currently run cantera 1.55 through Matlab 6.1, and it works great. 
Look back at your path settings--to get the demos to run, I had to
include the folder 

C:\Program Files\Cantera\demos\MATLAB

Including 'C:\Prog... demos\' or other higher-level folders didn't do
the trick; I had to include the specific '...demos\MATLAB' folder. 
If I deleted it and tried to run the demo 'catcomb.m', I got the
following error:

??? Undefined function or variable 'catcomb'.

Also, do the regular functions from the toolbox work?  (probably the
simplest to check is 'gasconstant.m'--just type 'gasconstant'
[without the single quotes] and press enter).  If so, this would
almost certainly point to a problem in the matlab path.

Good luck,
Steven DeCaluwe
